<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-735-404  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 735 404.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Nov 1989 v6 n11 p202(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Erasable optical disk drives. (Hardware Review) (REO-650; JasmineDirectOptical; Genesis 6000; Cirrus 600 Magneto Optical Drive)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pogue, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Five erasable optical disk drives for the Apple Macintosh arereviewed: Pinnacle Micro's $4,995 REO-650, Jasmine Technologies'$4,995 DirectOptical, Macsetra Technologies' $4,995 Genesis 6000,Sumo Systems' $4,595 RSSM 600B and La Cie's $4,995 Cirrus 600Magneto Optical Drive.andP;  Optical disk subsystems are sold byvendors rather than OEMs, and the vendor is responsible for addingthe fan, housing, controller software, and documentation.andP;  Thedrives themselves are currently made only by Sony and Ricoh.andP;  ThePinnacle drive is rated best since its Sony disk format isslightly faster than Ricoh disks and holds 25 to 50Mbytes more percartridge.andP;  Its controller software is intuitive and runssmoothly.andP;  The other four drives use the Ricoh disk format.andO;Jasmine's software is poor, and the unit is overpriced.andP;  TheMacsetra drive lacks an eject button.andP;  Sumo's unit is a goodall-around choice and the La Cie drive an excellent value.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pinnacle Micro Inc. (products)Jasmine Technologies Inc. (products)MACsetra Technologies International Inc. (products)Storage Plus Inc. (products)La Cie Ltd. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (equipment and supplies)Pinnacle Micro REO-650 (Disk drive)Jasmine Technologies DirectOptical (Disk drive)Sumo Systems RSSM600B (Optical disk drive)Cirrus 600 Magneto Optical Drive (Disk drive).andO;Topic:     Erasable Optical MemoryOptical DisksEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Top opticals. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>